In moments of rest god impregnated me with a brilliant brand @modernblkgirl that’s changing millions of lives. If It wasn’t for 2020, I wouldn’t of heard that little voice in my head pushing me to start MBG. 

The word talks about resting on the 7th day. It’s bigger than church but we all ignore it. It’s about giving your mind time to regroup, recollect,and to rejuvenate your spirit. GRIND CULTURE IS FOOLISHNESS. Hard work without passion or vision is wasted time. Your passion and vision comes from your heart that you can’t hear from/distinguish because you are always moving!!!

When I listened to that word on rest by Micheal Todd, It forced me to think about all the amazing companies that came from global stillness!! 

Take time for yourself. Less is more. Stop burning out. REST!!!! Your next big grand idea is coming!!! Take this video as a sign 🖤

Vulnerable Moment: If you have been in any of my classes, I always say learning how God speaks to you is crucial. In the past few months, I've been feeling stagnant and uncomfortable. I've been feeling like I'm not doing enough. My new daily Mantra is " Show up in your true potential every day'. Then, last night before bed, something told me to pull Modernblkgirl numbers. I can confirm we have taught over 400,000 Women Globally. My goal was to always get to 500,000 in 5 years. Our third anniversary is on November 20th.

If you remember my earlier days on Clubhouse, I NEVER in a million years thought we would be here. I was in absolutely no shape to be a CEO and Founder. I was just a girl from Brooklyn who loved numbers and proving people wrong. However…the community of amazing Black women said, "Nope, you are ready. Teach us, and we will guide and follow you". Three years later, we have won so many awards.. we have been featured worldwide. MY goodness! To the thousands of black women out there who championed me, I thank God for you. 

Some words I want to leave you guys with.

Comparison Robs Joy.
It takes a village.
Be anchored in Faith.
Trust the process.
